node.title: Public libraries in Nelson now subject to vaccine pass checks
node.description: People in Nelson need to show vaccine passes to enter public libraries after the Covid-19 outbreak in the region.

node.title: Omicron yet to prove more severe than other variants - WHO
node.description: World Health Organisation spokesperson Dr Margaret Harris says the Covid-19 Omicron variant has "many more mutations" but it is yet to be found to be more severe than previous variants. Audio

node.title: Myanmar’s ousted president and the capital’s mayor were convicted, too.
node.description: The court also convicted U Win Myint, the former president, who was found guilty of violating Covid-19 protocols; and U Myo Aung, the ousted mayor of Naypyidaw, who was convicted of incitement.

node.title: Solomon Islands Prime Minister survives vote of no confidence after deadly anti-government riots
node.description: Prime Minister Manasseh Sogavare has survived a motion of no confidence in Solomon Island's Parliament after the majority of MPs backed the leader at the centre of recent civil unrest.

node.title: Myanmar court sentences ousted leader Suu Kyi to four years in prison
node.description: A court in Myanmar sentences the country's ousted leader, Aung San Suu Kyi, to four years in prison after finding her guilty of incitement and violating coronavirus restrictions.

node.title: Former Canberra football coach sends himself to jail for child sex abuse
node.description: Stephen Porter asked the ACT Supreme Court to send him to jail immediately, even though he hasn't yet been sentenced for his child abuse crimes.

node.title: Illawarra coal mine deemed of 'state significance'
node.description: The fate of the Dendrobium coal mine expansion is in the hands of the NSW Planning Minister after new declaration means the Independent Planning Commission's initial objection could be ignored.

node.title: Queensland's reopening and border bubble rules explained
node.description: Queensland is bringing forward its much-awaited reopening, dropping border restrictions for all interstate travellers from December 13, four days earlier than predicted — and opening up the NSW border zone for residents.

node.title: 'Caution has paid off' with positive start under traffic light system - PM
node.description: Jacinda Ardern says the first weekend in the traffic light system has received largely positive feedback. Audio

node.title: Why France faces so much anger in West Africa

node.title: Pharmac secures Pfizer's Covid-19 medication, subject to Medsafe approval - PM
node.description: The government has purchased 60,000 courses of Pfizer's oral antiviral medication to treat early infections of Covid-19, subject to Medsafe approval, Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern has confirmed.

node.title: Covid-19 update: 135 new community cases in NZ today

node.title: 'An uber-geeky committee': The MPs scrutinising the Covid-19 rules

node.description: Bob Dole, who overcame grievous World War Two combat wounds to become a pre-eminent figure in US politics as a longtime Republican senator from Kansas and his party's unsuccessful 1996 presidential…

node.title: Southland school, kindergarten locked down after firearms incident
node.description: A school and kindergarten in Winton, Southland, were in lockdown this afternoon after a firearms incident left one person injured, according to police.

node.title: What’s on TV This Week: ‘Landscapers’ and ‘Live in Front of a Studio Audience’
node.description: David Thewlis and Olivia Colman star in a true-crime mini-series on HBO. And an ABC special brings back the 1980s sitcoms “The Facts of Life” and “Diff’rent Strokes.”

node.title: Child among five people injured in multi-vehicle crash
node.description: Emergency services are working to free multiple people trapped after a major crash on the Calder Freeway, north-west of Melbourne.

node.title: Julia Gillard among international flight passengers into Adelaide sent to hotel quarantine after Omicron concern
node.description: Former prime minister Julia Gillard is one of many overseas arrivals sent to hotel quarantine in Adelaide despite having prior approval to isolate at home.

node.title: United States pushes back on New Zealand and allies' hopes of joining AUKUS
node.description: One of America's most senior military commanders dismisses suggestions the AUKUS security partnership could soon be expanded to include other allies such as New Zealand or Japan.

node.title: Perth loses fifth Ashes Test due to WA quarantine rules, no decision on replacement venue
node.description: Cricket Australia confirms that the fifth and final Ashes Test will not be held at Perth Stadium, following the WA government's requirement for all players, staff and broadcasters to quarantine for 14 days after arriving in the state.

node.title: Public school teachers in NSW are striking tomorrow — here's everything you need to know
node.description: Teachers will join thousands of other public servants taking industrial action tomorrow and parents are being warned to make alternative care plans for the day.

node.title: Ajaz Patel's 10 wickets hard to believe, says spinner's proud father

node.title: Why it's a great time to be a Spider-Man fan
node.description: A stack of Spider-Man-related movies are set to swing into cinemas, and fans of the web-spinning superhero couldn't be happier.

node.title: DVA admitted liability for soldier's PTSD 18 months after he took his own life, royal commission told
node.description: Lance Corporal Ryan Goodwin sought compensation from the Department of Veterans Affairs for his post-traumatic stress disorder in 2018, but by the time the department admitted liability this year he had been dead for 18 months.

node.title: The man who sparked a three-day lockdown pleads guilty over quarantine breach

node.title: Labor says it won't negotiate its 43 per cent emissions reduction target, as it stares down government attack
node.description: Scott Morrison was quick to attack Labor's commitment to reduce emissions by 43 per cent by 2030, calling it an "opening bid" which could be pushed higher if Labor has to negotiate with the Greens to form government. But Labor says that won't happen.

node.title: Solomon Islands PM excoriated during confidence debate
node.description: The Solomon Islands prime minster came under searing criticism as he faced a confidence vote in parliament today.

node.title: How TikTok Keeps You Watching
node.description: It’s the most successful video app in the world. Our columnist has obtained an internal company document that offers a new level of detail about how the algorithm works.

node.title: Queensland borders will reopen to interstate COVID-19 hotspots from next Monday

node.title: Man who fatally beat, dragged wife 70 metres along Darwin's Mindil Beach pleads guilty
node.description: The NT Supreme Court hears the man, who pleaded guilty to reckless manslaughter, dragged his wife into shallow water on the popular Darwin beach before running to higher ground and claiming to witnesses that she'd drowned
